3.20	Train_horn	Train horn	Train horns are audible warning devices found on most diesel and electric locomotives. Their primary purpose is to alert persons and animals to the presence of a train, especially when approaching a grade crossing. They are also used for acknowledging signals given by railroad employees (i.e. during switching operations).	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/f/f8/Nathan_M5.JPG/300px-Nathan_M5.JPG
